1
00:00:01,210 --> 00:00:03,740
(Episode 84)

2
00:00:04,340 --> 00:00:07,980
Alright,
it's time to be honest with myself.

3
00:00:09,110 --> 00:00:11,950
I can't keep living like this anymore.

4
00:00:19,390 --> 00:00:20,390
Honey?

5
00:00:21,030 --> 00:00:24,360
- Hurry and eat. You have to get to work.
- Yes, okay.

6
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:27,170
Oh, my.

7
00:00:28,930 --> 00:00:30,800
Is this stuff for the dry cleaner's?

8
00:00:38,840 --> 00:00:40,410
Oh, my, what's this?

9
00:00:41,680 --> 00:00:44,380
Oh, my. Look at him.

10
00:00:48,320 --> 00:00:51,190
He must've bought this
for our upcoming anniversary.

11
00:00:53,690 --> 00:00:55,360
What a sweet man.

12
00:00:59,630 --> 00:01:03,840
To think he got me this amazing gift
and just played it cool.

13
00:01:06,970 --> 00:01:08,070
Honey!

14
00:01:11,010 --> 00:01:13,680
- Honey!
- Yes? What is it?

15
00:01:14,180 --> 00:01:16,410
- What's with the good mood?
- You bet there is.

16
00:01:17,450 --> 00:01:19,980
You're such a sweetheart.

17
00:01:20,650 --> 00:01:24,290
I'm so proud to be married
to a man like you.

18
00:01:25,290 --> 00:01:28,030
What's with the sudden compliments?
Are you feeling okay?

19
00:01:28,190 --> 00:01:31,500
There you go again, playing dumb.

20
00:01:32,930 --> 00:01:37,840
Is there anything you want?
Whatever you want, I'll buy it for you.

21
00:01:38,940 --> 00:01:41,010
I don't think I need anything.

22
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:43,210
Are you trying to buy me a gift
or something?

23
00:01:43,410 --> 00:01:48,050
Yes! Because you're so cute.
No, no, because you're so sweet.

24
00:01:50,980 --> 00:01:53,490
Seriously, what's gotten into you
all of a sudden?

25
00:01:56,860 --> 00:01:59,720
Here.
You should be the one to put it on me.

26
00:02:01,230 --> 00:02:02,230
Go on.

27
00:02:05,630 --> 00:02:09,130
Honey, are you someone
who goes through my pockets?

28
00:02:11,070 --> 00:02:14,340
What happened to respecting
each other's privacy?

29
00:02:15,640 --> 00:02:16,640
What?

30
00:02:17,540 --> 00:02:18,880
My gosh.

31
00:02:23,450 --> 00:02:24,650
What's gotten into him?

32
00:02:29,650 --> 00:02:33,120
(Caution: High-temperature Steam)

33
00:02:34,260 --> 00:02:37,430
(Caution: High-temperature Steam)

34
00:02:38,930 --> 00:02:40,270
Alright, just stick close to me.

35
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:42,970
Please. I'm fine.

36
00:02:44,300 --> 00:02:46,700
Director Ma. This way, please.

37
00:02:47,070 --> 00:02:48,870
Right, okay.

38
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:19,940
(Caution: High-temperature Steam)

39
00:03:24,410 --> 00:03:25,510
Darn it!

40
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:37,320
Jun Ho!

41
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:40,160
Jun Ho! Are you okay?

42
00:03:40,590 --> 00:03:43,060
Here! Over here! Hurry!

43
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:45,930
Someone call an ambulance! Hurry!

44
00:03:46,970 --> 00:03:49,300
- Seo Rin...
- What?

45
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:53,740
Oh no. Jun Ho! What do I do?

46
00:03:53,810 --> 00:03:57,980
Jun Ho!

47
00:03:58,780 --> 00:04:00,080
Somebody call an ambulance!

48
00:04:01,350 --> 00:04:02,610
Hurry!

49
00:04:03,210 --> 00:04:04,220
Oh Jang Mi.

50
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:06,990
Today's the day
I ruin that pretty little face of yours.

51
00:04:07,820 --> 00:04:09,590
How dare you step out of line
and challenge me?

52
00:04:10,790 --> 00:04:11,960
You're going to get what you deserve.

53
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:18,500
CEO Chae.
It's an emergency. It's about Jun Ho...

54
00:04:19,100 --> 00:04:20,870
What? What happened to my Jun Ho?

55
00:04:21,630 --> 00:04:23,500
There was an accident in the laundry room.

56
00:04:24,340 --> 00:04:27,170
- He was burned.
- What? My Jun Ho?

57
00:04:27,840 --> 00:04:30,170
(Korea University Hospital)

58
00:04:32,580 --> 00:04:35,550
- Please, Jun Ho.
- CEO Chae.

59
00:04:36,550 --> 00:04:38,720
Please, calm down.
You're going to hurt yourself.

60
00:04:39,780 --> 00:04:41,350
Do you think I care about
getting hurt right now?

61
00:04:41,790 --> 00:04:45,920
Jun Ho is the one who's hurt!
I have to know how badly he's injured.

62
00:04:46,520 --> 00:04:48,190
This is when you need to be calm.

63
00:04:48,830 --> 00:04:50,190
There are too many people watching.

64
00:04:50,730 --> 00:04:53,160
Are you going to announce to everyone
that Jun Ho is your son?

65
00:05:11,550 --> 00:05:14,420
No. You must be in so much pain.

66
00:05:16,490 --> 00:05:18,220
Please, do everything you can for him.

67
00:05:18,490 --> 00:05:21,330
- Please, do everything you can.
- Ma'am, you need to wait outside.

68
00:05:22,060 --> 00:05:24,660
What happened?
How did you get hurt so badly?

69
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:28,100
Who were you trying to save
that you'd let this happen?

70
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:32,870
Did you even think about your mother?

71
00:05:33,570 --> 00:05:37,710
Did you ever stop to think
how much this would break my heart?

72
00:05:38,140 --> 00:05:40,880
Why did you get hurt instead of that girl?
Why?

73
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:52,720
Are you still sulking?

74
00:05:53,760 --> 00:05:56,290
Pouting? Of course not.

75
00:05:57,830 --> 00:06:00,770
I was just checking your pockets
before taking them to the dry cleaner's.

76
00:06:00,830 --> 00:06:03,400
I wasn't snooping through your pockets
on purpose.

77
00:06:04,670 --> 00:06:05,670
I know.

78
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:07,110
I'm sorry, honey.

79
00:06:08,140 --> 00:06:11,110
You were planning to surprise me
for our anniversary...

80
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:15,950
and do something grand,
but I went and spoiled it.

81
00:06:19,080 --> 00:06:20,750
I won't do it again, okay?

82
00:06:21,690 --> 00:06:25,790
Hey, it's fine, really. I'm not mad.
It's all good.

83
00:06:36,430 --> 00:06:37,540
You're here, Mom.

84
00:06:40,340 --> 00:06:42,910
Why on earth did that steam pipe
suddenly burst right at us?

85
00:06:43,270 --> 00:06:46,810
We need to get to the bottom of this.

86
00:06:47,380 --> 00:06:49,250
Someone could have done this on purpose.

87
00:06:49,510 --> 00:06:51,050
Who would do something
like that on purpose?

88
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:53,020
It was you, Chae Hwa Young. You did this.

89
00:06:53,520 --> 00:06:55,220
I was your target, wasn't I?

90
00:06:55,950 --> 00:06:56,950
But too bad for you.

91
00:06:57,620 --> 00:06:58,960
Your precious son got hurt instead.

92
00:06:59,260 --> 00:07:02,590
I've given him a painkiller,
so he should be in less pain now.

93
00:07:03,760 --> 00:07:04,760
Okay, thank you.

94
00:07:11,540 --> 00:07:15,140
A laundry room machine malfunctions
in a top-tier hotel? Seriously?

95
00:07:15,610 --> 00:07:17,280
Jun Ho was injured on the job.

96
00:07:17,540 --> 00:07:19,310
How could you let
the facility management get this bad?

97
00:07:19,540 --> 00:07:22,880
As the hotel's CEO,
doesn't this fall on you, Mom?

98
00:07:23,350 --> 00:07:24,680
How can you say something like that?

99
00:07:25,020 --> 00:07:28,150
Oh Jang Mi,
it should have been you who got hurt.

100
00:07:28,620 --> 00:07:30,690
So why was it my Jun Ho instead of you?

101
00:07:31,460 --> 00:07:32,660
You cunning little witch.

102
00:07:33,190 --> 00:07:35,660
You deliberately put my son
in harm's way, didn't you?

103
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:37,430
You've got to be kidding me, Mom.

104
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,300
Aren't you even going to ask if I'm okay?

105
00:07:39,930 --> 00:07:41,800
I could've been seriously injured.

106
00:07:42,270 --> 00:07:44,770
But you're not worried about
your own daughter's well-being at all.

107
00:07:45,070 --> 00:07:46,970
You only seem to feel sorry
for your subordinate,

108
00:07:46,970 --> 00:07:48,070
General Manager Kang Jun Ho.

109
00:07:48,510 --> 00:07:51,040
- What's with that look on your face?
- Do you think I'm blind?

110
00:07:51,610 --> 00:07:54,550
I can see you're perfectly fine,
so why would I ask?

111
00:07:55,050 --> 00:07:57,280
General Manager Kang is the one
who got hurt instead of you.

112
00:07:57,550 --> 00:08:00,220
Is showing concern for an injured person
now a reason to pick a fight?

113
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:02,650
It is when you don't even bother
to ask if I'm okay.

114
00:08:03,220 --> 00:08:04,520
You don't think
I was scared out of my mind?

115
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:06,320
Chae Hwa Young?

116
00:08:06,620 --> 00:08:07,630
Don't you dare.

117
00:08:10,090 --> 00:08:12,600
Fine. You must have been
very frightened too.

118
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:15,630
Getting you to say that
was like pulling teeth.

119
00:08:17,170 --> 00:08:19,240
If General Manager Kang
hadn't shielded me,

120
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:21,670
my face would've been horribly burned.

121
00:08:21,910 --> 00:08:23,370
That's exactly what I was hoping for.

122
00:08:23,910 --> 00:08:25,480
You darn witch, Oh Jang Mi.

123
00:08:26,140 --> 00:08:27,980
I guess that makes General Manager Kang
your savior, then.

124
00:08:28,380 --> 00:08:32,320
He saved your pretty little face
from being ruined. What a hero, right?

125
00:08:33,320 --> 00:08:35,950
You'd better be grateful to him
for the rest of your life.

126
00:08:43,230 --> 00:08:44,830
I've been trying to reach you.
Why weren't you answering?

127
00:08:45,030 --> 00:08:46,130
What is it? What's wrong?

128
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:48,270
It's about Jun Ho.
He's in the hospital right now.

129
00:08:49,130 --> 00:08:52,870
- Jun Ho? Why?
- I guess he's playing Prince Charming.

130
00:08:53,340 --> 00:08:56,540
He burned his arm protecting Seo Rin
from a blast of steam.

131
00:08:56,770 --> 00:08:57,810
A burn?

132
00:08:58,110 --> 00:08:59,640
Wait, what about Director Ma? Is she okay?

133
00:09:00,650 --> 00:09:02,210
Seo Rin's fine, apparently.

134
00:09:02,810 --> 00:09:05,850
Although she's by his side,
taking devoted care of him now.

135
00:09:06,850 --> 00:09:11,090
Anyway, thanks for telling me.
Can you text me which hospital he's at?

136
00:09:16,490 --> 00:09:17,500
Jun Ho.

137
00:09:18,160 --> 00:09:20,100
If you're so determined
to be the Prince Charming,

138
00:09:20,530 --> 00:09:23,200
you'd better make sure
you win over Ma Seo Rin for good.

139
00:09:23,940 --> 00:09:25,540
Because I need to have Baek Ho for myself.

140
00:09:27,940 --> 00:09:31,410
- What? Jun Ho was hit by steam?
- Oh, my goodness.

141
00:09:32,640 --> 00:09:34,780
How bad is the burn?

142
00:09:35,350 --> 00:09:38,920
- No, I can't just stand here.
- Hey, wait, honey.

143
00:09:39,150 --> 00:09:40,520
I'll go get the car.

144
00:09:40,520 --> 00:09:42,420
- Dad, please look after Mom.
- Okay.

145
00:09:43,420 --> 00:09:44,790
Honey, calm down.

146
00:09:55,700 --> 00:09:56,700
My son.

147
00:09:58,700 --> 00:10:00,600
Only when you're lying here in pain...

148
00:10:01,570 --> 00:10:02,940
can I finally touch you.

149
00:10:04,480 --> 00:10:05,480
Jun Ho.

150
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,350
My son.

151
00:10:16,750 --> 00:10:17,790
My son.

152
00:10:22,090 --> 00:10:23,460
Thank you for growing up so well...

153
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:26,800
and for becoming such a fine man.

154
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:29,970
I truly mean it.

155
00:10:31,500 --> 00:10:32,770
I mean it, Ha Neul.

156
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:46,880
I will make sure you inherit Dream Group.

157
00:10:48,620 --> 00:10:51,390
It's the only way I can make it up to you.

158
00:10:53,260 --> 00:10:54,260
This marriage...

159
00:10:55,330 --> 00:10:57,760
is just a means to that end.

160
00:10:58,930 --> 00:11:00,660
Just use her and toss her aside, Ha Neul.

161
00:11:02,330 --> 00:11:03,730
Please, wake up, Ha Neul.

162
00:11:06,670 --> 00:11:07,670
Chae Hwa Young.

163
00:11:08,340 --> 00:11:10,840
So, Jun Ho is the most important person
in the world to you.

164
00:11:11,940 --> 00:11:12,940
If...

165
00:11:13,210 --> 00:11:15,850
you were to lose that precious person,
or have him taken from you,

166
00:11:16,610 --> 00:11:19,250
that would be the most painful revenge,
wouldn't it?

167
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:23,020
For causing my father's death
and what you did to my mother,

168
00:11:23,620 --> 00:11:26,160
you deserve to know
what pain feels like too, don't you?

169
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:35,970
Even one-hundredth of my pain...

170
00:11:36,570 --> 00:11:38,670
No, even one-thousandth of it,
you deserve to feel it.

171
00:11:39,070 --> 00:11:41,570
Don't you think? That would only be fair.

172
00:11:43,910 --> 00:11:46,310
Jang Mi. Are you all right?

173
00:11:47,310 --> 00:11:48,410
Baek Ho.

174
00:11:48,950 --> 00:11:51,820
You're all right, aren't you?
You're not hurt anywhere, are you?

175
00:11:54,190 --> 00:11:56,820
Thank goodness. I'm so relieved.

176
00:12:00,830 --> 00:12:04,260
General Manager Kang took the full blast
of steam for me,

177
00:12:05,060 --> 00:12:06,360
and he got burned.

178
00:12:06,630 --> 00:12:09,600
I just spoke with the doctor.
They said my brother will be fine.

179
00:12:11,270 --> 00:12:14,540
Jun Ho even beat leukemia.
This is nothing.

180
00:12:15,410 --> 00:12:17,840
I see. You should get back to him.

181
00:12:18,380 --> 00:12:21,210
Your parents must be very worried.

182
00:12:21,580 --> 00:12:24,420
Please tell your parents I'm sorry.

183
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:28,650
It was just a minor incident.

184
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:30,120
Don't worry about it.

185
00:12:30,820 --> 00:12:31,820
All right?

186
00:12:35,990 --> 00:12:37,600
- Four.
- Mom!

187
00:12:37,660 --> 00:12:38,730
- Six.
- Mom!

188
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:40,330
- Seven, eight.
- Mom!

189
00:12:40,330 --> 00:12:42,130
What's with all the fuss?

190
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:46,000
Jun Ho burned his arm protecting Seo Rin
and was rushed to the hospital.

191
00:12:46,170 --> 00:12:47,540
They're both at the hospital now.

192
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:49,570
What? What are you talking about?

193
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:53,280
Jun Ho and Seo Rin were in the laundry
when there was a steam accident.

194
00:12:53,340 --> 00:12:57,380
Seo Rin almost got hit in the face,
but Jun Ho pulled her close and saved her.

195
00:12:57,450 --> 00:12:59,750
My goodness. I can't believe it.

196
00:13:00,380 --> 00:13:02,850
Hey, this Jun Ho is quite the man.

197
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:07,120
- Now that's a real man.
- Jun Ho seems cold on the outside,

198
00:13:07,420 --> 00:13:09,090
but it seems when he falls for someone,
he falls hard.

199
00:13:10,090 --> 00:13:14,130
So to Seo Rin,
Jun Ho is a total lifesaver.

200
00:13:15,230 --> 00:13:17,330
Mom, don't you start calling him
so casually.

201
00:13:17,940 --> 00:13:21,140
Seriously,
you never get anyone's title right.

202
00:13:21,540 --> 00:13:24,010
- Like how you call Tae Pyung casually.
- Wait a minute.

203
00:13:24,610 --> 00:13:27,240
General Manager Kang saved our Seo Rin?

204
00:13:27,950 --> 00:13:31,650
Apparently, he got hurt saving her.

205
00:13:35,020 --> 00:13:36,020
Jun Ho.

206
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:38,960
Jun Ho!

207
00:13:40,620 --> 00:13:41,630
You're here.

208
00:13:42,790 --> 00:13:43,830
Oh, my goodness!

209
00:13:44,330 --> 00:13:46,530
How badly is my Jun Ho hurt?

210
00:13:47,030 --> 00:13:48,370
I just spoke with his doctor.

211
00:13:48,630 --> 00:13:51,440
He's in some pain from the burns,
but he'll be fine soon.

212
00:13:51,640 --> 00:13:53,800
- So don't worry too much.
- I'm so sorry.

213
00:13:54,770 --> 00:13:56,310
This incident happened at our hotel,

214
00:13:56,870 --> 00:13:59,340
I can't tell you how sorry I am.

215
00:13:59,340 --> 00:14:00,440
My Jun Ho.

216
00:14:01,450 --> 00:14:02,750
How did this happen?

217
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:06,280
This is our company's responsibility
and my oversight. Forgive me.

218
00:14:06,650 --> 00:14:08,550
We will take care of everything.

219
00:14:10,690 --> 00:14:13,190
You must be very alarmed by this,
CEO Chae.

220
00:14:14,190 --> 00:14:17,090
We'll take it from here.
I know you're busy.

221
00:14:17,700 --> 00:14:18,800
You can get back to work.

222
00:14:26,540 --> 00:14:28,510
Which of you are the patient's family?

223
00:14:29,510 --> 00:14:33,480
- That's us.
- The patient is in a lot of pain,

224
00:14:33,540 --> 00:14:36,280
so we're going to give him another dose
of painkillers.

225
00:14:36,580 --> 00:14:40,780
He's going through a lot right now
and needs his rest.

226
00:14:41,090 --> 00:14:44,460
I'll have to ask everyone to leave
except for his mother.

227
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:48,190
But I'm Jun Ho's mother!

228
00:14:59,870 --> 00:15:04,510
Jun Ho and Seo Rin went
to the laundry room and burned his arm.

229
00:15:04,740 --> 00:15:07,580
Gosh, how can this happen?

230
00:15:07,850 --> 00:15:10,210
What about my Seo Rin? Is she all right?

231
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:14,750
- She's probably fine.
- What do you mean "probably?"

232
00:15:15,150 --> 00:15:17,190
That means you didn't see for yourself.

233
00:15:17,350 --> 00:15:19,990
CEO Chae went to the hospital...

234
00:15:20,420 --> 00:15:23,190
Well, since the accident happened
while he was saving Seo Rin,

235
00:15:23,260 --> 00:15:25,560
so Seo Rin must be fine.

236
00:15:25,660 --> 00:15:26,900
Good grief!

237
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:30,430
If it were Hong Ju who was hurt,
would you be so casual about it?

238
00:15:30,530 --> 00:15:32,470
Of course not!

239
00:15:33,640 --> 00:15:36,570
I can't just sit here.
I need to see her for myself.

240
00:15:36,870 --> 00:15:37,880
Where's Seo Rin?

241
00:15:38,310 --> 00:15:40,280
- Over there.
- Grandfather!

242
00:15:40,340 --> 00:15:42,950
Seo Rin! Let me get a look at you.

243
00:15:43,210 --> 00:15:46,020
Are you okay? You're not hurt anywhere?

244
00:15:46,620 --> 00:15:50,250
I'm fine. I just stopped by
because I knew you'd be worried, Grandpa.

245
00:15:50,450 --> 00:15:55,190
Good. You're perfectly fine.
That's a relief.

246
00:15:55,360 --> 00:15:59,130
You gave me quite a scare.
My heart nearly stopped.

247
00:15:59,330 --> 00:16:02,270
We can't have your heart stopping,
Grandfather.

248
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:05,940
You're right.

249
00:16:09,410 --> 00:16:10,410
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

250
00:16:10,410 --> 00:16:15,010
My Jun Ho got hurt
because of that cunning vixen, Oh Jang Mi.

251
00:16:16,080 --> 00:16:17,080
That's it.

252
00:16:18,050 --> 00:16:20,980
She pushed Jun Ho
to save herself, didn't she?

253
00:16:22,290 --> 00:16:24,150
- Ma'am.
- That must be it.

254
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:26,960
She's exactly the kind of witch
who would do something like that.

255
00:16:27,290 --> 00:16:30,060
She made my Jun Ho get hurt
to save her own skin.

256
00:16:30,290 --> 00:16:32,730
That's not what happened.

257
00:16:33,630 --> 00:16:36,230
General Manager Kang was injured
trying to save Oh Jang Mi.

258
00:16:36,300 --> 00:16:37,870
No. You're wrong.

259
00:16:38,470 --> 00:16:42,210
Are you trying to tell me
that Jun Ho is actually in love with her?

260
00:16:42,370 --> 00:16:44,740
And he'd throw himself in harm's way
to save Oh Jang Mi?

261
00:16:45,310 --> 00:16:46,540
That's impossible. Not my son.

262
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:48,050
If he's truly in love,

263
00:16:49,250 --> 00:16:50,250
then it's possible.

264
00:16:50,580 --> 00:16:51,580
What are you talking about?

265
00:16:52,650 --> 00:16:54,650
Because of some worthless little tramp
like Oh Jang Mi,

266
00:16:54,890 --> 00:16:58,490
you think my Jun Ho would be that reckless
with his own life?

267
00:16:59,990 --> 00:17:01,730
We should have them get married
as soon as possible.

268
00:17:01,890 --> 00:17:04,800
No. I'll never let him marry Oh Jang Mi.

269
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:10,570
If my Jun Ho truly would die for her,

270
00:17:10,570 --> 00:17:12,740
do you think
I'm crazy enough to let them marry?

271
00:17:12,770 --> 00:17:13,870
Then what's the plan?

272
00:17:14,710 --> 00:17:17,410
Don't we need at least one heir
to Chairman Ma's bloodline?

273
00:17:17,910 --> 00:17:20,380
That's why we have to find
the real Seo Rin.

274
00:17:21,080 --> 00:17:24,450
As soon as we find her,
I'll get rid of Oh Jang Mi.

275
00:17:25,250 --> 00:17:29,120
I've been passing Jang Mi off as Seo Rin
to Chairman Ma.

276
00:17:29,250 --> 00:17:32,560
Once we find the real Seo Rin,
Oh Jang Mi will no longer be needed.

277
00:17:33,360 --> 00:17:35,030
Yes, that's true, but...

278
00:17:35,090 --> 00:17:38,600
That's how it was 30 years ago,
and it's the same now.

279
00:17:39,430 --> 00:17:42,470
I don't need two of them.
I've only ever needed one.

280
00:17:43,330 --> 00:17:46,070
Understood? Absolutely no twins.

281
00:17:46,340 --> 00:17:48,110
I only need one.

282
00:17:49,440 --> 00:17:50,440
I'm so sorry.

283
00:17:50,840 --> 00:17:53,010
You're in so much pain because of me,
aren't you?

284
00:17:55,350 --> 00:17:56,880
I guess getting hurt has its perks.

285
00:17:57,410 --> 00:17:58,920
Why would you do something so reckless?

286
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:01,050
What would you have done
if it was your face and not your arm?

287
00:18:02,620 --> 00:18:03,620
Good point.

288
00:18:04,250 --> 00:18:05,860
My face is the only thing
I've got going for me.

289
00:18:07,420 --> 00:18:09,430
How can you be joking at a time like this?

290
00:18:09,930 --> 00:18:11,930
I'm just glad you're safe, Seo Rin.

291
00:18:13,100 --> 00:18:16,170
I hope I can repay you for this someday.

292
00:18:17,970 --> 00:18:19,700
So you see this as something you owe me?

293
00:18:21,170 --> 00:18:22,510
To me, it was pure instinct.

294
00:18:23,310 --> 00:18:25,610
The instinct to protect the one I love.

295
00:18:28,050 --> 00:18:29,080
Anyway...

296
00:18:34,220 --> 00:18:36,720
You should rest up. I'll get going.

297
00:18:37,220 --> 00:18:38,620
You're leaving the moment I wake up?

298
00:18:39,020 --> 00:18:40,260
That's so cold.

299
00:18:40,260 --> 00:18:41,930
I'll stay with you tonight.

300
00:18:42,990 --> 00:18:43,990
Well then.

301
00:18:56,040 --> 00:18:59,140
Is he a baby? What are you going to do,
coming all the way here at this hour?

302
00:19:00,240 --> 00:19:02,980
I'll stay with him. Don't worry, Mom.
You should get some sleep.

303
00:19:05,050 --> 00:19:06,650
Okay, then come first thing
tomorrow morning.

304
00:19:08,050 --> 00:19:09,120
Was that your mother?

305
00:19:09,690 --> 00:19:10,690
Yes.

306
00:19:11,490 --> 00:19:12,890
My brother was sick as a kid...

307
00:19:12,890 --> 00:19:15,060
and had to be hospitalized
for a long time.

308
00:19:15,790 --> 00:19:17,590
He absolutely hates hospitals,

309
00:19:18,060 --> 00:19:19,800
so she's worried
and insists on coming over tonight.

310
00:19:21,700 --> 00:19:22,700
I see.

311
00:19:24,470 --> 00:19:28,210
Looks like Ssangkal's girlfriend
cleared out her place and vanished.

312
00:19:28,410 --> 00:19:31,680
They didn't go after
Shin Ae Ran too, right?

313
00:19:31,680 --> 00:19:32,910
That can't happen.

314
00:19:35,580 --> 00:19:38,050
General Manager Kang Jun Ho
is Chae Hwa Young's son.

315
00:19:38,580 --> 00:19:40,080
How am I supposed to tell Baek Ho?

316
00:19:40,850 --> 00:19:41,850
- Jang Mi.
- Baek Ho.

317
00:19:42,950 --> 00:19:43,950
Yes?

318
00:19:44,690 --> 00:19:46,520
Weren't you about to tell me something?

319
00:19:46,890 --> 00:19:47,890
It's nothing.

320
00:19:48,390 --> 00:19:49,460
What about you?

321
00:19:49,790 --> 00:19:51,860
You must've been very scared.
Go get some rest.

322
00:19:54,330 --> 00:19:55,330
Okay.

323
00:20:20,990 --> 00:20:23,960
No need to hide it. Is it a crime to eat?

324
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:26,160
Yeom San Wol.

325
00:20:26,700 --> 00:20:28,200
You've certainly got some nerve.

326
00:20:28,730 --> 00:20:31,840
What if Father sees the photos of you
and throws you out?

327
00:20:32,070 --> 00:20:33,440
You're really living it up, aren't you?

328
00:20:33,570 --> 00:20:36,310
A person should eat.
It's not like being all prim and proper...

329
00:20:36,370 --> 00:20:38,080
doesn't put food on the table, does it?

330
00:20:38,080 --> 00:20:40,640
Just let me live a little, seriously.

331
00:20:40,710 --> 00:20:42,950
You make it sound like
you can't even breathe.

332
00:20:43,550 --> 00:20:47,150
Who else in your position
lives as well as you do?

333
00:20:47,220 --> 00:20:51,250
You're always going on about my "place."

334
00:20:51,320 --> 00:20:53,420
What's so wrong with my place?
You think you're so high and mighty?

335
00:20:53,490 --> 00:20:55,990
I'm pretty great in my own right.
What's your deal?

336
00:20:56,060 --> 00:20:57,290
Who do you think you are,
raising your voice?

337
00:20:57,730 --> 00:20:58,960
What's gotten into you?

338
00:20:59,260 --> 00:21:00,260
CEO Chae.

339
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:04,570
You're going too far.
It's not as if we did anything wrong.

340
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:09,140
You're only the CEO at the office.
Here, I'm the Chairman's daughter.

341
00:21:09,210 --> 00:21:11,070
Have you all lost your minds?

342
00:21:12,740 --> 00:21:13,780
"The Chairman's daughter?"

343
00:21:14,780 --> 00:21:17,850
That only applies
when you keep your promise to me.

344
00:21:19,420 --> 00:21:22,990
I told you to find Oh Jang Mi ages ago.
What are you still doing here?

345
00:21:23,350 --> 00:21:26,790
Is this any time to be eating chicken?
I gave you that order ages ago!

346
00:21:26,890 --> 00:21:30,060
- About that...
- CEO Chae.

347
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:32,130
My dear daughter-in-law.

348
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:33,660
Here's the thing.

349
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:35,900
Looks like you're finally getting it.

350
00:21:37,130 --> 00:21:39,440
One week. I'll give you exactly one week.

351
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:42,810
Find Oh Jang Mi within that time.
Understood?

352
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:49,810
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

353
00:21:52,580 --> 00:21:53,950
Tok Hee's asleep.

354
00:21:55,290 --> 00:21:58,520
<i>Hush now</i>

355
00:21:58,760 --> 00:21:59,890
Mom, what are you doing?

356
00:22:00,590 --> 00:22:03,030
Don't wake Tok Hee. Be quiet.

357
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:18,510
I should probably look into ways
to bring Seo Rin home.

358
00:22:19,410 --> 00:22:25,620
<i>When Mommy's in the island's shade</i>

359
00:22:26,480 --> 00:22:31,020
<i>Gathering oysters from the sea</i>

360
00:22:38,160 --> 00:22:40,000
My little Ok Hee and Tok Hee.

361
00:22:50,540 --> 00:22:52,680
<i>Hush-a-bye</i>

362
00:22:53,280 --> 00:22:54,310
<i>Hush-a-bye</i>

363
00:22:56,810 --> 00:23:00,020
Chae Hwa Young, that witch gave me
half of my wrinkles.

364
00:23:01,520 --> 00:23:05,320
She acts like she's so high and mighty.
Who does she think she is?

365
00:23:05,760 --> 00:23:07,190
Seriously, who knows where
she crawled out from...

366
00:23:08,660 --> 00:23:12,900
Mom, CEO Chae constantly blackmailed me
with the photos of you.

367
00:23:13,360 --> 00:23:15,200
I can't take this anymore.

368
00:23:15,470 --> 00:23:19,100
Unbelievable.
What a way to ruin a perfectly good meal.

369
00:23:19,870 --> 00:23:20,940
But, Mom.

370
00:23:21,370 --> 00:23:23,970
What if we really can't find out
where Oh Jang Mi is?

371
00:23:25,110 --> 00:23:28,450
Then CEO Chae will tell the Chairman
and expose all your photos.

372
00:23:28,550 --> 00:23:31,650
Don't even say things like that.
You'll jinx it.

373
00:23:32,080 --> 00:23:34,380
First things first,
let's go back to that side dish shop.

374
00:23:35,820 --> 00:23:37,250
Unbelievable.

375
00:23:53,840 --> 00:23:54,910
Find her now.

376
00:23:55,210 --> 00:23:58,010
Find her now. I said find my Seo Rin
this instant.

377
00:23:58,610 --> 00:24:02,150
Before that wench Oh Jang Mi
pretends to be our Seo Rin...

378
00:24:02,910 --> 00:24:05,820
and sinks her claws into Jun Ho
any deeper. Find her now!

379
00:24:05,920 --> 00:24:07,720
It seems we couldn't find her...

380
00:24:07,720 --> 00:24:09,290
because we only looked for
patients in their 30s.

381
00:24:10,050 --> 00:24:12,260
I'll immediately expand the search
to all age groups.

382
00:24:12,720 --> 00:24:13,960
Please, just give me a little more time.

383
00:24:14,690 --> 00:24:16,560
I need you to find my Seo Rin now.

384
00:24:17,490 --> 00:24:21,930
How else am I supposed to
get rid of Oh Jang Mi? Find her now!

385
00:24:38,520 --> 00:24:41,020
Mom, we just go to
Oh Jang Mi's side dish shop, right?

386
00:24:41,120 --> 00:24:44,890
Yes. I might as well go there
and stake out the place.

387
00:24:45,160 --> 00:24:47,860
How else are we going to find out
which hospital she's in?

388
00:24:48,460 --> 00:24:49,730
Come on, hurry up and get in.

389
00:25:10,150 --> 00:25:11,620
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

390
00:25:11,680 --> 00:25:14,990
The patient is having a seizure.
I think you need to come in.

391
00:25:17,820 --> 00:25:20,590
Isn't that Tae Pyung?
Where's he going this early?

392
00:25:21,260 --> 00:25:22,460
Probably making a delivery or something.

393
00:25:22,790 --> 00:25:25,560
No, I don't think so.
They're not open yet.

394
00:25:25,630 --> 00:25:27,260
This place doesn't open until 11.

395
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:30,300
The things you remember, Mom.

396
00:25:31,170 --> 00:25:32,170
Hey!

397
00:25:32,470 --> 00:25:35,940
Mom, you don't think he's going to see
Oh Jang Mi, do you?

398
00:25:36,370 --> 00:25:38,410
Oh my, he just might be.

399
00:25:39,010 --> 00:25:42,550
Hong Ju, hurry and follow him.
Let's tail him discreetly.

400
00:25:42,610 --> 00:25:43,610
Okay.

401
00:25:44,510 --> 00:25:46,950
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

402
00:25:47,520 --> 00:25:48,690
Stay on his tail.

403
00:26:15,380 --> 00:26:17,180
Hong Ju, we're saved!

404
00:26:18,210 --> 00:26:19,950
Mom, we're saved!

405
00:26:20,450 --> 00:26:21,450
We're saved!

406
00:26:34,330 --> 00:26:36,900
First, let's go inside and confirm it.

407
00:26:37,370 --> 00:26:38,370
Right.

408
00:26:38,970 --> 00:26:42,010
Mom, why am I so excited? We're saved!

409
00:26:42,070 --> 00:26:43,640
Hey, it's more than just being saved!

410
00:26:43,940 --> 00:26:47,140
Let's find Oh Jang Mi and present her
to the Chairman before anyone else.

411
00:26:47,440 --> 00:26:50,880
What will that wench Chae Hwa Young do?
She'll have to tuck her tail and run.

412
00:26:50,980 --> 00:26:55,150
I'm so thrilled.
I feel like a huge weight has been lifted.

413
00:26:55,590 --> 00:26:57,990
That's right.
The mystery of why CEO Chae had twins...

414
00:26:58,020 --> 00:26:59,890
but only raised one of them...

415
00:27:00,220 --> 00:27:03,130
will be solved once we find Oh Jang Mi
and take her to the Chairman, right?

416
00:27:04,030 --> 00:27:05,530
Let's go.

417
00:27:38,600 --> 00:27:39,700
Did you?

418
00:27:39,700 --> 00:27:42,130
You found the rehabilitation hospital
where Seo Rin is?

419
00:27:42,430 --> 00:27:43,430
Yes.

420
00:27:43,970 --> 00:27:45,400
I followed Oh Tae Pyung,

421
00:27:46,300 --> 00:27:47,640
and he led me
to a rehabilitation hospital.

422
00:27:50,870 --> 00:27:52,340
If Oh Tae Pyung went in,

423
00:27:52,340 --> 00:27:54,310
that has to be the hospital
where Seo Rin is.

424
00:27:54,740 --> 00:27:57,210
Manager Lee, so where is it?

425
00:27:58,280 --> 00:28:00,980
Did Manager Lee find Seo Rin's hospital?

426
00:28:25,840 --> 00:28:27,380
(The First Man)

427
00:28:27,440 --> 00:28:28,610
Baek Ho, didn't I tell you?

428
00:28:28,910 --> 00:28:31,980
- To stay away from Seo Rin.
- I just needed to talk to her in private.

429
00:28:32,050 --> 00:28:34,350
Stop it. Both of you, just stop it.

430
00:28:34,820 --> 00:28:38,960
Kang Jun Ho, you gave the right answer.
You passed the test.

431
00:28:39,160 --> 00:28:42,660
Have Seo Rin start preparing
for her wedding with Kang Jun Ho.

432
00:28:42,890 --> 00:28:45,200
Tae Pyung, we must move Seo Rin.
Right now.

433
00:28:45,360 --> 00:28:47,960
Manager Lee found out where she is.
She's in danger.

434
00:28:49,770 --> 00:28:51,770
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
